<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-09-18</DATELINE><TITLE>Biomarkers of Pulmonary Diseases</TITLE><BODY>Lungs and airways are affected by several pathologies, the most important of which are inflammation, infection and cancer. Some of the biomarkers of these pathologies are similar to those found in involvement of other organs. This chapter will briefly discuss general issues of biomarkers of pulmonary disorders listed in Table 16.1. Biomarkers of lung cancer are described in Chapter 13.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>